2A60QcsJtlE.description:
Ninotchka movie clips: http://j.mp/17HLmQu
BUY THE MOVIE: http://j.mp/17HLmQo
Don't miss the HOTTEST NEW TRAILERS: http://bit.ly/1u2y6pr

CLIP DESCRIPTION:
Ninotchka (Greta Garbo) is put off by Leon's (Melyvn Douglas) blatant efforts to flirt with her when all she wants are directions to the Eiffel Tower.

FILM DESCRIPTION:
"Garbo Laughs!" declared the ads for Ninotchka. In the face of dwindling foreign revenues, MGM decided to put Greta Garbo, a bigger draw in Europe than the US, in a box-office-savvy comedy, engaging the services of master farceur Ernst Lubitsch to direct. The film opens in Paris during the aftermath of the Russian revolution. A trio of Russian delegates (Sig Rumann, Felix Bressart, and Alexander Granach) are sent to Paris to sell the Imperial Jewels for ready cash. Grand Duchess Swana (Ina Claire), who once owned the jewels, sends her boyfriend Count Leon (Melvyn Douglas) to retrieve the diamonds, and he turns the trio into full-fledged capitalists, wining and dining them all through Paris. Moscow then dispatches the humorless, doggedly loyal Comrade Ninotchka (Garbo) to retrieve both the prodigal Soviets and the gems. When Leon turns his charm on Ninotchka, she regards him coldly, informing him that love is merely a "chemical reaction." Even his kisses fail to weaken her resolve. Leon finally wins her over by taking an accidental fall in a restaurant, whereupon Ninotchka laughs for the first time in her life. She goes on a shopping spree and gets drunk, while Leon begins falling in love with her in earnest. As a bonus to the frothy script, by Billy Wilder and others, and its surefire star power, Ninotchka features what is perhaps Bela Lugosi's most likeable and relaxed performance.

lhnOqZQya-Y.description:
in this tutorial I demonstrate how to create a two toned alternating checkered pattern using whipped cream. So easy to do and the cake itself takes probably less than 10 minutes to decorate.

for more dessert inspiration and for tutorial sneak peeks, visit:
http://www.instagram.com/rosiesdessertspot
http://www.facebook.com/rosiesdessertspot
http://www.pinterest.com/rosiesds
http://www.rosiesdessertspot.com

to view how to make an ice cream cake, please see this video below:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bOQonD0DqwI

Ingredients to decorate this cake:
600ml heavy cream
3 tablespoons caster sugar
1 tsp vanilla extract
purple soft gel food colour (or mix red and blue)

for the sign, I used fondant and wafer printed which has edible ink printed onto it. I will soon be offering a printing service from my website if you guys need any edible signs printed, hopefully by October or so.

Thanks for tuning in guys, I hope you liked this tutorial! Apologies for the old style of video, I had made this one in advance just in case there was a Saturday upload I couldn't get to in time. There have been some personal family and health related problems here at the moment, but all is slowly sorting itself out. 

Thanks again, and I shall see you next time! xxx

A bográcsba olajat öntünk és megpároljuk rajta a finomra vágott hagymát. Hozzáadjuk a lebőrözött, kicsontozott majd kockára vágott csirkecombot és átsütjük, közben hozzáadjuk a fűszereket, a tárkony kivételével. UcsRqnS_kQE.title: HP Future Classroom 教學預覽 | Engadget 中文版
UcsRqnS_kQE.description:
現在就訂閱 Engadget 中文版吧！http://goo.gl/69kUk

HP 打造首間未來教室，硬體到位的初嘗試（影片）：http://goo.gl/1DPSB

一直以來，台灣的電腦教室都僅供電腦課程來使用，但隨著家庭擁有個人電腦的比例與數量大幅提升，新世代的兒童與青年可以說是從小就生長在這個環境下，猶如呼吸般自然的「數位世代」，輕鬆地操作這些電子設備，這讓電腦教室的性質也應該開始有所轉變。加上觸控與雲端技術的發展，提供整個教育課程教授方法翻新的可能性。如何運用？HP 與台北市私立立人國際國民中小學合作打造一間「未來教室」，跳轉過後來看看他們如何將科技融入教育中。
